rsgain
------------------------------------------
rsgain (really simple gain) is a ReplayGain 2.0 command line utility for
Windows, macOS, Linux, BSD, and Android. rsgain applies loudness metadata tags
to your files, while leaving the audio stream untouched. A
ReplayGain-compatible player will dynamically adjust the volume of your tagged
files during playback.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.0-1
  libavcodec61-7.1.1-1
  libavformat61-7.1.1-1
  libavutil59-7.1.1-1
  libebur128_1-1.2.6-1bl2
  libfmt11-11.1.2-1bl1
  libgcc1-12.4.0-3
  libinih0-57-1
  libstdc++6-12.4.0-3
  libswresample5-7.1.1-1
  libtag2-2.0.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.44-1
  cmake-3.28.3-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  gcc-g++-12.4.0-3
  libavcodec-devel-7.1.1-1
  libavformat-devel-7.1.1-1
  libavutil-devel-7.1.1-1
  libebur128-devel-1.2.6-1bl2
  libfmt-devel-11.1.2-1bl1
  libinih-devel-57-1
  libswresample-devel-7.1.1-1
  libtag-devel-2.0.2-1
  ninja-1.12.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/complexlogic/rsgain

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/complexlogic/rsgain/archive/refs/tags/v3.6.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack rsgain-3.6-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./rsgain-3.6-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/rsgain-3.6-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/rsgain-3.6-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(rsgain)
  /usr/bin/rsgain.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/rsgain.README
  /usr/share/doc/rsgain/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/rsgain/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/rsgain.1.gz
  /usr/share/rsgain/presets/default.ini
  /usr/share/rsgain/presets/ebur128.ini
  /usr/share/rsgain/presets/loudgain.ini
  /usr/share/rsgain/presets/no_album.ini

